# Use Graphite for Git Operations

When the user gives any git command (or asks for git operations), use **Graphite CLI** (`gt`) instead of raw `git` where applicable.

## Mapping

| Git command / intent             | Use instead                                   |
| -------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `git checkout -b feature/xyz`    | `gt branch create feature/xyz`                |
| Create branch stacked on current | `gt branch create feature/xyz`                |
| Rebase / pull latest             | `gt sync`                                     |
| Push and open PRs                | `gt submit`                                   |
| `git status` (stack view)        | `gt log` or `gt stack`                        |
| Switch branch                    | `gt checkout <branch>` or `gt up` / `gt down` |

## BREE Branch Naming

Always follow this convention for BREE monorepo branches:

```
feature/<app>/<description>    e.g. feature/talent-village-ai/code-snippets
fix/<app>/<description>        e.g. fix/bree-api/nats-reconnect
chore/<scope>/<description>    e.g. chore/fly/update-dockerfile
```

## When to use raw git

- `git add`, `git commit` — use as-is
- `git diff`, `git log` (non-stack) — use as-is
- Operations Graphite doesn't cover — fall back to `git`

